of Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite, of the kindred of Ram: against Job was his wrath kindled, because he justified himself rather than God.","year":-1520},{"id":"recGJgXlFaUBmeOuc","ref":"Job.32.3","text":"Also against his three friends was his wrath kindled, because they had found no answer, and yet had condemned Job.","year":-1520},{"id":"recrS0TBSMy1ImK7V","ref":"Job.32.4","text":"Now Elihu had waited till Job had spoken, because they were elder than he.","year":-1520},{"id":"recm5lyTnPXljXtHv","ref":"Job.32.5","text":"When Elihu saw that there was no answer in the mouth of these three men, then his wrath was kindled.","year":-1520},{"id":"reclmwBQJbQYsDruX","ref":"Job.32.6","text":"And Elihu the son of Barachel the Buzite answered and said, I am young, and ye are very old; wherefore I was afraid, and durst not shew you mine opinion.","year":-1520},{"id":"rechXmHHEY0RosG2P","ref":"Job.32.7","text":"I said, Days should speak, and multitude of years should teach wisdom.","year":-1520},{"id":"recYAfVMA8gNQfAPN","ref":"Job.32.8","text":"But there is a spirit in man: and the inspiration of the Almighty giveth them understanding.","year":-1520}]}
